      • getAbiKey

        Optional<Sha1HashCode> getAbiKey()
        Returns a SHA-1 hash that represents the ABI for the Java files returned by getJavaSrcs(). If getJavaSrcs() returns an empty collection, then this will return a non-absent value. The only requirement on the hash is that equal hashes imply equal ABIs.

        Because the ABI is computed as part of the build process, this rule cannot be invoked until after this rule is built.

        Returns Optional.absent() if the rule did not build successfully, or if the ABI could not be extracted for any reason.
